HEADWORD: Exsiccation
<hw>Ex`sic*ca"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>exsiccatio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>exsiccation</ets>.]</ety> <def>The
act of operation of drying; evaporation or expulsion of moisture; state
of being dried up; dryness.</def> <rj><au>Sir T. Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
